{
  "texts": [
    "2b, but with an increased object phase contrast, α test, chosen within a range between 1 and 1.999 (i.e., ϕ ∈ [0, 2π)).",
    "The corresponding results are shown as the blue curve in Fig. 4a, illustrating a degradation in the imaging performance of the diffractive model as α test increases.",
    "This degradation is relatively minor in the PSNR results for the amplitude channel but more pronounced for the phase channel.",
    "Specifically, as α test increases from 1 to 1.5, the average amplitude PSNR value slightly drops from 17.04 to 15.82, while the phase PSNR falls from 15.06 to 11.96.",
    "When α test approaches 2, the average amplitude and phase PSNR values further decrease to 15.34 and 9.87, respectively."
  ]
}